data.description: Under contract-accepting backup offers. Welcome to this lovely Spring Hill home that is both cozy and spacious. Besides the curb appeal, a classic barrel portico entryway welcomes you to 1900+ square feet where you’ll find 3 large bedrooms, 2 baths, and a 3-car garage; a portion of which can serve as that workshop you’ve always wanted! With updates that include NEW ROOF BEING INSTALLED APRIL 2024, NEWER carpeting in the bedrooms, NEWER interior and exterior paint, NEWER vinyl flooring, and a NEWER A/C unit installed in 2019, you’ll have plenty of time to enjoy your morning coffee from the screened lanai while overlooking your landscaped grounds. The kitchen is bright and open, featuring stainless steel appliances, recessed lighting, a walk-in pantry, and a convenient casual dining bar for those breakfasts on the go! When hosting parties and dinners you’ve got a formal dining area as well as extra space off the kitchen to accommodate your guests. The open and bright family room is wired for surround sound and gives access to the lanai area through sliding doors.  There’s even a great den that makes for an ideal home office, a personal gym, a music room, or a 4th bedroom. Both baths are spotless with the master boasting a wonderful soaking tub and a walk-in shower. Unlike many homes where the washer and dryer are in the garage, you’ll love the laundry room that offers access into the garage. Besides the LOW quarterly HOA fees (that include basic cable) and no CDD fee, this Spring Hill neighborhood is well located. Reach Mary Giella Preparatory school and Classical Preparatory school via the community’s walking path or check out the middle and high schools that are also highly rated. Quail Ridge is a charming, gated community nestled along a conservation area and accompanied by an assortment of biking and walking paths. Residents are free to board their golf carts to explore the ponds to fish, the playground to spend sunny afternoons, and the woodlands to catch glimpses of local wildlife. Jump on any number of nearby thoroughfares (I-75, I-4, Suncoast Parkway, I-275) to explore Florida, or take a 35-minute ride to Tampa International Airport. From your location, you are still a short drive to Home Depot, as well as a wealth of restaurants, medical facilities, country clubs and parks, and the one-of-a-kind Gulf of Mexico. There’s nothing NOT to love about this home and its encompassing amenities.
